It wasn't a difference of 5% vs 2%. What I listed was actually stated on the Dev corner. Their numbers even. <br>
<br>
They were seeing the difference between 5/100 and 3.6/75. <br>
But rather than actually doing the math properly, they were taking the straight difference of 5-3.6, not (5/100 - 3.6/75) which would have been 0. They made a very simple mistake in their math because they were dealing with percentages. So the hybrids will move up 5% (or 2% if it is really that) of their previous value and the pure melee will move up 5% (or two if it is really only 2%) of their previous value. <br>
<br>
The percentages are totally equal for hybrids and pure melee on this. With this AA ability (if it goes live) all melee can improve their physical enhancement stats by 5% (or if it is only 2%, then 2%) of what it was without this. <br>
<br>
And yes, VI needs to learn how to do simple algebra.<br>
<br>
