<br>
Right now, the only thing that a warrior can tank better than a Paly or an SK is something that hits so hard it requires defensive to slow the damage. Of course, when you use defensive, dps is lowered and aggro control becomes even more of an issue. Fights in a smaller group will drag out longer with the warrior using defensive because other members have to avoid out taunting the warrior and then what have you really saved? With a paly or sk, the cleric will have to step up the heals, but doesn't have to worry about being beat on nearly as much or not being able to sit between heals. The rest of the group can really open up with the damage and can debuff and slow as early as they want. In the end the mob dies much faster and both time and mana are saved. With my warrior, I may have to taunt multiple times to get the mob off an enchanter, or hope for a lucky proc to do the work for me. With my paladin, I just drop a couple of stuns and in less time than it takes taunt to refresh the chanter can sit down and med. I don't know of anything in this game that a single group with a warrior tanking can do that a single group with a paly or sk tanking can't. If they could actually tank any more, there wouldn't be a need for warriors in the game at all. <p><i>"All priests should offer a similar level of value in solo, group, and raid situations, and they won't be considered balanced until this is true." Rich Waters</i><br><br><font size="+1"><i><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="-1"><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=153420>Talyena Trueheart</a>, Hierophant of Tunare<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203026>Tresha Trueheart</a>, Warlord for Erollisi Marr<br>Dawntreaders, Terris-Thule</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udobbanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>i